  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Immediate Response to Chile Earthquake</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project  is to ensure a rapid and quality response by Oxfam to the needs of the Chilean population affected by the 8.8 Richter scale earthquake of 27th February just off the west coast of Chile, near the city of Concepcion, which also produced a Tsunami causing significant damage to coastal communities.    Since the intervention is of a relatively limited scale and timeframe, it will be  kept to a simple WASH intervention, with an advocacy component, building simply on the capacity that was installed in the region and which would permit a safe, effective intervention with limited risks of creating unmanageable situations</narrative>
  </description>
